SIMPLE: imparity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imparity
<hw>Im*par"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> + <ets>parity</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>imparit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inequality;
disparity; disproportion; difference of degree, rank, excellence,
number, etc.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lack of comparison, correspondence, or suitableness;
incongruity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In this region of merely intellectual notion we are at once
encountered by the <qex>imparity</qex> of the object and the faculty
employed upon it.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Indivisibility into equal parts; oddness.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impark</ent>⟦br⟧
